---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Design Options — Greg Brewer"
  description="Three landing page design explorations for Greg Brewer's personal site."
>
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 py-16 space-y-10">

    <div>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Design Options</h1>
      <p class="text-base-content/70 mt-3 leading-relaxed">
        Three distinct layout approaches for Greg Brewer's landing page. Each uses the same content
        but differs in visual hierarchy, grid structure, and personality. Use the theme switcher in
        the nav to preview how each option responds to all 14 configured themes.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">

      <a href="/" class="card bg-base-200 border border-base-300 hover:border-primary hover:shadow-md transition-all block group">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
            <div class="space-y-2">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="badge badge-primary">Option A</span>
                <span class="badge badge-ghost">Current</span>
              </div>
              <h2 class="text-xl font-bold group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">Minimal / Focused</h2>
              <p class="text-base-content/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                Centered single-column layout with generous whitespace. Content flows as you scroll.
                Feels like a senior engineer's personal page — confident, unhurried, precise.
              </p>
              <ul class="text-sm text-base-content/60 space-y-1 mt-2">
                <li>Single column, centered, max-width constrained</li>
                <li>Large whitespace between sections</li>
                <li>Profile photo + name centered at top</li>
                <li>Clean dividers between sections</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-base-content/30 group-hover:text-primary transition-colors shrink-0 mt-1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M9 18l6-6-6-6"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a href="/designs/option-b" class="card bg-base-200 border border-base-300 hover:border-secondary hover:shadow-md transition-all block group">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
            <div class="space-y-2">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="badge badge-secondary">Option B</span>
              </div>
              <h2 class="text-xl font-bold group-hover:text-secondary transition-colors">Editorial / Magazine</h2>
              <p class="text-base-content/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                Asymmetric two-column grid with blog content given newspaper-front-page weight.
                Feels like someone who writes and thinks publicly — expressive, content-forward.
              </p>
              <ul class="text-sm text-base-content/60 space-y-1 mt-2">
                <li>2/3 + 1/3 asymmetric column grid</li>
                <li>Featured post card at top of writing section</li>
                <li>Left-aligned identity block, inline with content</li>
                <li>Strong typographic contrast between heading sizes</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-base-content/30 group-hover:text-secondary transition-colors shrink-0 mt-1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M9 18l6-6-6-6"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a href="/designs/option-c" class="card bg-base-200 border border-base-300 hover:border-accent hover:shadow-md transition-all block group">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
            <div class="space-y-2">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="badge badge-accent">Option C</span>
              </div>
              <h2 class="text-xl font-bold group-hover:text-accent transition-colors">Dashboard / Builder's Workbench</h2>
              <p class="text-base-content/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                Responsive card grid — every section is a distinct panel. Information-dense on
                desktop, everything visible at a glance. Feels like a builder's control panel.
              </p>
              <ul class="text-sm text-base-content/60 space-y-1 mt-2">
                <li>2–3 column card grid on desktop, single column mobile</li>
                <li>Each section is a DaisyUI card component</li>
                <li>Stats strip with "30+ years", role, project highlights</li>
                <li>Lessi AI as a featured wide card at top</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-base-content/30 group-hover:text-accent transition-colors shrink-0 mt-1" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M9 18l6-6-6-6"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

    </div>

    <p class="text-sm text-base-content/50">
      All options use DaisyUI semantic color tokens — theme switching works identically on every design.
    </p>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
